An Act exempting disabled veterans from sales tax when leasing a motor vehicle.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Section 6 of chapter 64H of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2014 Official Edition,
2 is hereby amended by striking out subsection (u) and inserting in place thereof the following
3 subsection:-
4 (u) Sale of a motor vehicle purchased by or leased to and for the use of a person who has
5 been determined by the United States Department of Veterans Affairs to have a permanent
6 service-connected disability. This exemption shall apply to 1 motor vehicle only owned or leased
7 and registered for the personal, noncommercial use of such person.
